@node sysreq "PhoneBook Version 1.00   System Requirements"

PhoneBook needs Workbench 2.04+ and ReqTools library v38+ (included).

@endnode
@node feat "PhoneBook Version 1.00   Features"

 o Small, quick and easy to use
 
 o Completely font sensitive
 
 o Will load and save PhoneIt phone books
 
 o Uses reqtools requesters
 
 o Will load a fone book on start up
 
 o Very small file size
 
 o Example databases supplied
 
And more i've forgotten...

@endnode
@node quick "PhoneBook Version 1.00   Quick Tutorial"

Click on the Add button. The window title will change giving you
instructions on what to do. Enter a name into the Name string gadget and
a phone number in the Number string gadget. Once you are satisfied with
what you have entered, click on the Add button again. Our Database contains
one record now. Create a few more just to get the hang of it.

Now, we'll save the database. Click on the save button and a requester will
open prompting for the save format. Press Enter or click on the PhoneBook v1
gadget. This will save the file in PhoneBook's own format. A file requester
will now pop up and you can select the filename to save to.

You've just created and saved your first PhoneBook database. That wasn't
too hard was it ?

@endnode
@node mainw "PhoneBook Version 1.00   The Main Window"

When you first start PhoneBook, a number of the gadgets on the main window
will be ghosted. This is because there is no current database in memory.
When you load or create a new database the gadgets will become available.

There are 12 button gadgets, 2 string gadgets and a text box. Along the top
of the window is the main gadgets. These are for (from left to right)
creating records, deleting records, deleting entire database, searching,
printing (see the "Print Window" section) and going to a particular record.

The top most string gadget will be used for the name of the person and the
second is for the phone number. Next to the Number string gadget is a text
box which displays the current/total record. Next to these are the Next and
Previous gadgets for moving through the database a record at a time.

Along the bottom we have gadgets for Loading, Saveing, About and Quit.

@{"Click here" system "Sys:Utilities/Multiview >NIL: MainWindow.iff"} to see the main window.

@endnode
@node pwin "PhoneBook Version 1.00   The Print Window"

The print feature is only available in the registered version.

There is 1 MX gadget, 2 integer gadgets and 2 button gadgets. The MX is for
selecting whether to print the entire database or just a range. When you
enter the print window, it defaults to All and the From and To integer
gadgets' values will be as if you've selected all.

When you are happy with the range settings, click on print to print or
cancel to cancel. When you click on print a requester will pop up telling
you to make the printer ready and give you one last chance to cancel.

@endnode
@node swin "PhoneBook Version 1.00   The Search Window"

The search feature is only available in the registered version.

When the search window is open, you can still use the main window normally.
When it first opens the Find string gadget is selected for you. Type in
what you want to find and click on either Name or Number. The search will
start from the current record so when you've found what you're looking for
you can just hit either Name or Number again and it will find the next
occurence if there is one. When one has been found, the display will show
the record that the search was found in.

NOTE: The search is currently CASE SENSITIVE.

@endnode

@node ft "PhoneBook Version 1.00   Filetypes"

PhoneBook will load its own custom format files, PhoneIt v1.3 and NComm v3
phone books. You can save in PhoeBook's custom format and PhoneIt v1.3
compatible files only. This is because the NComm phonebooks have alot more
information in them then PhoneBook uses.

When you load a PhoneBook, its file type is automaticly detected and the
window title changes to tell you the type it's loading. You'll get an
unknown fileformat error if PhoneBook doesn't recognise the file format.

@endnode

@node tt "PhoneBook Version 1.00   ToolTypes"

PhoneBook supports the following ToolTypes:

LOAD=<path&filename to load>    Load a phonebook on startup.

@endnode

